            In this case, your certificate needs to be It is the Base64 encoding
            of the following JSON Object which is encoded in UTF-8:
            &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt; {&lt;br&gt;
            "data":"&lt;Base64-encoded-certificate&gt;",&lt;br&gt;
            "dataType":"pfx",&lt;br&gt;
            "password":"&lt;pfx-file-password&gt;"&lt;br&gt;}
            &lt;br&gt; To install certificates on a virtual machine it is
            recommended to use the [Azure Key Vault virtual machine extension for
            Linux](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/virtual-machines/extensions/key-vault-linux)
